      <item>
        <title>Panning advice?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[anon41616463]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Just as a rule of thumb, you shouldn’t really pan your bass. By leaving it in the center, you’ll get the best low-end projection from stereo speakers/headphones. Of course there are exceptions (I’ve heard panning effects in some dubstep basses, but they’re very subtle).</p>
          <p><a href="https://disco.auxy.co/t/panning-advice/1375/3">Read full topic</a></p>
